<%- include('partials/head') %>

<body>
    <%- include('partials/nav') %>

    <main class="page-shell">
        <section class="page-hero compact-hero">
            <p class="eyebrow">About PantryWizard</p>
            <h1>About / Help</h1>
            <p>
                PantryWizard is a recipe discovery web app that helps users decide what to cook based on ingredients they already have.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section two-column">
            <article class="info-card">
                <h2>What PantryWizard does</h2>
                <p>
                    PantryWizard helps users search for recipes using ingredients on hand, then narrow those results using filters such as cuisine and diet.
                    The goal is to make meal planning quicker, easier, and more practical.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The app is designed for busy users, beginner cooks, college students, and anyone who wants simple meal ideas without wasting ingredients.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="info-card">
                <h2>Who it is for</h2>
                <ul class="feature-list">
                    <li>College students looking for easy meal ideas</li>
                    <li>Busy users trying to cook quickly</li>
                    <li>Beginner cooks who want simple guidance</li>
                    <li>Users with dietary preferences or restrictions</li>
                </ul>
            </article>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <div class="section-heading">
                <p class="eyebrow">Instructions</p>
                <h2>How to use the app</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="steps-grid">
                <article class="info-card">
                    <span class="step-number">1</span>
                    <h3>Search ingredients</h3>
                    <p>Go to the Search page and enter one or more ingredients you already have in your pantry or fridge.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="info-card">
                    <span class="step-number">2</span>
                    <h3>Choose filters</h3>
                    <p>Select cuisine and diet preferences to narrow your results and find better recipe matches.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="info-card">
                    <span class="step-number">3</span>
                    <h3>Review recipes</h3>
                    <p>Look through the returned recipe cards to compare cooking time, ingredients used, and recipe details.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="info-card">
                    <span class="step-number">4</span>
                    <h3>Save favorites later</h3>
                    <p>Once the favorites feature is connected, users will be able to save meals and add notes for future use.</p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <div class="notice-card">
                <h2>Project status</h2>
                <p>
                    This page is fully styled and complete for the UI portion of the assignment. Dynamic favorites, notes, ratings,
                    and the final recipe detail route can be connected later without redesigning the page layout.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>

</html>
